  "text": "The cellular and molecular consequences of wnt signaling have been defined in some detail in epithelial stem cells and their progenitors, especially those of the colon. [CITATION_1] The general scheme of the canonical wnt pathway is that the exposure of cells to wnt protein inhibits the intracellular degradation of ␤-catenin. The accumulation of signaling-competent ␤-catenin allows the association with DNA-binding factors of the TCF/LEF (lymphoid enhancer factor) family and induces the transcription of downstream target genes. In contrast to epithelial cells, relatively little and somewhat controversial information is available regarding the role and importance of this pathway for T-cell development.",
